@kathleenhensley5951  I don't think this generation is too disillusioned to accept Reeve's Superman. The movie and the characterization even with the somewhat dated special effects, still holds up because of the strength of the performances and how faithful it is to the source material and characterization of Superman. 

The issue is that the studio thinks that stories that did well in comics and animated films need to be warped to appeal to Modern Audiences - essentially reinventing the wheel. 

That strategy didnt work with 'Superman Returns' and as good as the trailers and the Henry Cavill casting was, it didnt work for 'Man of Steel'. All that is needed is to look at the Superman from a best selling comic run or Superman from the Bruce Timm animated series or the Superman from 'Superman vs. The Elite' and copy it verbatim in live-action.
